data.description: 1898 Victorian in the historic district and close to town. Large city lot .21 of an acre. This lovely lady has many of the original features like original woodwork, pocket doors, door fixtures, plates and door knobs, some light fixtures, claw foot tub in master bath, wavy glass windows, beautiful wood floors in living room and sitting room. Also features high ceilings. Master bath was gutted and rebuilt. New sewer lines have been installed. There is a 2 car garage and a shed/shop. The home should be financeable with a conventional loan but not VA or FHA. Help make this home one of charming beauties in the neighborhood. There is another dwelling on the property but it is not livable so please don't go inside. Seller is motivated.
